OK here is a brief definition of what this is for you young guys that do not know. Back in the day officers did not have collapsible batons to carry . title: For Sale:  Chinese steel core 7.62 x 39, 500 rounds for $300
postcontent:
I have 500 rounds of Chinese steel core "copper washed" 7.62 x 39. The headstamp of 31 93 indicates that it was made in factory 31 in 1993. The Chinese ammo I purchased in the early 1990's came in yellow or green boxes that were marked "Norinco" and "non-corrosive." 1990's manufacture should be non-corrosive.

This is excellent, reliable ammo but because of the steel core it should not be used for shooting steel reactive targets. Check out this video (not mine) shooting steel plates of various thickness: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hPucq_H73v8

This ammo was banned from importation by the BATF in the mid 1990' but it is legal to buy, sell, own and shoot it. 

The ammo is loose packed in ten bags of 50 rounds. 500 rounds for $300.
